 and cook <b>25 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add cornflour to yoghurt and stir until well combined. Carefully transfer 2 cups of the hot stock mixture from mixing bowl into jug with yoghurt and stir to combine with aid of spatula."},{"content":"Mix <b>6 min\/80°C\/\/speed 1<b>, slowly pouring yoghurt mixture through hole in mixing bowl lid."},{"content":"Add dried mint, salt and pepper and mix with aid of spatula, then cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b> or until rice is cooked and soup has thickened slightly. Divide soup between serving bowls. Garnish with chickpeas, spinach, fresh mint and parlsey. Drizzle with reserved Garlic and chilli oil before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or the <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","You can store any leftover oil in the refrigerator for up to 2 days. Discard garlic cloves before storing."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","50m","6 portions"]}